                                                                                                               Carnation pact with DC Design 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Sept. 21: Multi-brand car sales and services venture  Carnation Auto - today entered into a tie-up with Dilip Chhabrias DC Design to introduce customised solutions for car owners.        
	The solutions will enable customers to redesign cars  be it the Tata Nano or the Innova. The customised kits will be sold exclusively through Carnations nationwide network.         
	These solutions will answer the need for distinct identity, space, privacy, comfort, entertainment and utility. Additionally, these options will receive personalised attention at Carnations world-class car care back-up network anywhere in the country, said Jagdish Khattar, chairman and managing director of Carnation Auto.        
	First in the offering is the Innov8, based on the Toyota Innova. The interiors have been worked to include plush leather seats that recline up to 150 degress, a privacy partition, a 19-inch LCD TV with optional satellite TV, a sound system with DVD player, a beverages chiller, fold-out tables and ample leg room.        
	The semi-customised kits will include different front and rear bumpers, bonnet enhancements, side skirting and fog lamps with pseudo twin exhaust tips.         
	The kits are now available for the Honda City and the Suzuki Swift. The Tata Nano kit is being developed.                                                                                                                                        
